title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be any <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-000H.xml"
addr="ra-000H"
title="Integral domain">Integral domain</fr:link>. Then there exists a unique <fr:link
type="local"
href="field-0001.xml"
addr="field-0001"
title="Field">Field</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> (unique up to isomorphism) and an injection <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i\colon  R\hookrightarrow \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> such that for all other fields <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\varphi \colon  R\hookrightarrow \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex>, then there exists an extension <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\overline {\varphi }\colon \mathbb {F}\hookrightarrow \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> such that the following diagram commutes:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {array}{ccc}R & \xrightarrow {\varphi } & \Bbbk \\ \downarrow ^{i} & & \parallel \\ \mathbb {F} & \xrightarrow {\overline {\varphi }} & \Bbbk \end {array}]]></fr:tex><fr:p>We call <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> the <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Ring of Fractions</html:dfn> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
